Shops and schools are closed in the main city of Indian Kashmir in protest of
Israel's continuing air strikes on southern Lebanon.
The one-day strike Saturday in Kashmir's summer capital of Srinagar was called
by Syed Ali Geelani.  He heads the hard-line wing of the separatist alliance,
the All Parties Hurriyat Conference.
Angry protests were held in several parts of India Friday against Israel's
military action.  Protests erupted soon after Muslim prayers Friday afternoon
in Kashmir.
